      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>When crystals of pure <i>α</i>-glucose are dissolved in water, isomerization occurs slowly to produce <i>β</i>-glucose. Propose a mechanism for the isomerization.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbDBXIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--a3871282409b23330056cbb66ec51d95e2542386/OChem_19_EC_042.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction shows the interconversion of alpha-glucose and beta-glucose through a reversible reaction. The position of the hemiacetal hydroxyl group is axial in alpha and equatorial in beta.\">",
